## Architecture

```
GUI (Tkinter)
    ↓ writes
input.yaml          ← human-readable, editable by hand
    ↓ read by
pipeline_runner.py  ← orchestrates everything, calls all scripts in order
    ↓ calls
creator_optimiser_docker.sh
csv_editor__energy_comparator.sh
md_runner.sh
md_post_processor.sh
get_rdf.sh
trend_plotter.sh
summary_writer.py   ← new, collects all results
```

The GUI never calls scripts directly. It only writes `input.yaml` and then launches `pipeline_runner.py`. All logic lives in `pipeline_runner.py` which reads `input.yaml` and drives everything. This means you can also run headlessly by editing `input.yaml` manually and calling `python pipeline_runner.py` directly — no GUI needed.

