## GUI — what each section contains

### Tab 1: Structure
- File picker → `cif`
- Three spinboxes → `supercell [x, y, z]`

### Tab 2: Dopants
- Table widget, one row per dopant entry
- Columns: dopant, dopant_valency, host, host_valency, count, carrier, carrier_valency
- Add row / Remove row buttons
- Validation: all rows must share the same carrier, dopant ≠ host

### Tab 3: Distance Filters
- Six fields (dop_dop_min/max, dop_ion_min/max, ion_ion_min/max)
- Checkbox per field to enable/disable (maps to null when disabled)

### Tab 4: Relaxation & MD
- Dropdown for `relax_model` (1–8 with names from the registry)
- `max_files_per_folder` spinbox
- Checkbox `md_docker`
- List entry for `md_temperatures`
- Text field for `md_dump_pattern`

### Tab 5: RDF
- Checkbox `run_rdf`
- Radio: all pairs vs custom list
- Fields for `rdf_rmax`, `rdf_dr`

### Tab 6: Analysis
- Checkboxes: `run_msd_arrhenius`, `run_elastic`, `run_trend_plots`
- Fields: `conductivity_t_ref`, `msd_fit_start`, `msd_fit_end`
- Dropdown `carrier_species` (Li / Na / auto-detect)

### Tab 7: Stages
- Six checkboxes, one per stage — lets you rerun from any point

### Bottom bar (always visible)
- **Save input.yaml** button
- **Run pipeline** button → saves yaml then launches `pipeline_runner.py` in a subprocess
- Live log window (scrollable Text widget, streams stdout from `pipeline_runner.py`)
- Status indicator per stage (grey → running → green/red)

